{"entryType":"UniProtKB reviewed (Swiss-Prot)","primaryAccession":"C8WLM1","uniProtkbId":"CGR2_EGGLE","entryAudit":{"firstPublicDate":"2020-04-22","lastAnnotationUpdateDate":"2025-04-09","lastSequenceUpdateDate":"2009-11-03","entryVersion":71,"sequenceVersion":1},"annotationScore":5.0,"organism":{"scientificName":"Eggerthella lenta (strain ATCC 25559 / DSM 2243 / CCUG 17323 / JCM 9979 / KCTC 3265 / NCTC 11813 / VPI 0255 / 1899 B)","commonName":"Eubacterium lentum","taxonId":479437,"lineage":["Bacteria","Bacillati","Actinomycetota","Coriobacteriia","Eggerthellales","Eggerthellaceae","Eggerthella"]},"proteinExistence":"1: Evidence at protein level","proteinDescription":{"recommendedName":{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}],"value":"Digoxin reductase"},"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}],"value":"1.3.2.-"}]},"alternativeNames":[{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}],"value":"Cardenolide reductase"}},{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000303","source":"PubMed","id":"23869020"}],"value":"Cardiac glycoside reductase operon protein 2"}}],"flag":"Precursor"},"genes":[{"geneName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000303","source":"PubMed","id":"23869020"}],"value":"cgr2"},"orderedLocusNames":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000312","source":"EMBL","id":"ACV56484.1"}],"value":"Elen_2529"}]}],"comments":[{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}],"value":"Involved in the inactivation of the cardiac medication and plant natural product digoxin, thus decreasing drug efficacy and toxicity. Catalyzes the reduction of the alpha,beta-unsaturated butyrolactone ring of digoxin to the inactive metabolite dihydrodigoxin. Likely uses the cytochrome Cgr1 as the physiological electron donor, encoded by the adjacent gene in the locus. Only reduces digoxin and other cardenolide toxins, such as digitoxin, digoxigenin, ouabain and ouabagenin. Therefore is a specialized enzyme present in some gut bacteria E.lenta that protects their human host against ingested plant toxins"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"digoxin + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome c] + 3 H(+) = dihydrodigoxin + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome c]","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:62528"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:10350"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:14399"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29033"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29034"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:71002"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:145795"}],"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:62529"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"digitoxin + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome c] + 3 H(+) = dihydrodigitoxin + 2 Fe(III)-[cytochrome c]","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:62532"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:10350"},{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA-COMP:14399"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29033"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29034"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:145796"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:282234"}],"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000269","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"},{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:62533"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000305","source":"PubMed","id":"29761785"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"digoxigenin + 2 Fe(II)-[cytochrome c] + 3 H(+) = dihydrodigoxigenin + 2 Fe(